title.narrative: OUTPUT 6.2 - CP SERVICES

description.narrative: By 2024, accessible and quality birth registration and child protection (prevention and response) services are in place and delivered by qualified statutory and non statutory service providers in most disadvantaged localities in Liberia., which contributes to Access To Justice, Adolescent Empowerment, Harmful Practices (Fgm/C And Child Marriage), Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2024, boys and girls In Liberia have access to quality prevention and response services for violence, abuse and exploitation and for birth registration.
